Retrieve Subtree from Warehouse Hierarchy

A logistics company maintains a hierarchical storage system in its warehouse using a Binary Search Tree (BST). Each storage unit is uniquely identified by a number.

The hierarchy follows these rules:

For any storage unit:

All units with smaller IDs are located in the left subtree
All units with larger IDs are located in the right subtree


You are given the warehouse structure in level-order format, where:

Each value represents a storage unit ID
-1 represents a missing (null) node


Your Task

Construct the BST exactly as represented by the level-order input
Search for the storage unit with the given ID (val)


If found:

Print all storage units in its subtree using level-order traversal


If not found:

Print []
Input format :
First line: Integer n → number of storage units
Second line: n space-separated integers representing the hierarchical structure (level-order format, use -1 for null)
Third line: Integer val → target storage ID
Output format :
Print the subtree in level-order traversal
If the node is not found, print an empty list []
Code constraints :
1 ≤ n ≤ 5000
1 ≤ Node value ≤ 10^7
-1 represents no storage unit (null)
Structure always follows the warehouse hierarchy rule (BST property)
1 ≤ val ≤ 10^7
Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
5
4 2 7 1 3
2
Output 1 :
2 1 3
Input 2 :
7
5 3 8 2 4 7 9
3
Output 2 :
3 2 4


Solution:


#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class Node{
    public:
    int data;
    Node* left;
    Node* right;
    
    Node(int val){
        data = val;
        
        left = right = nullptr;
    }
};

Node* root = nullptr;

void insert(int val){
    
    Node* nn = new Node(val);
    
    if(root == nullptr){
        root = nn;
        return ;
    }
    
    Node* temp = root;
    
    while(true){
        
        
        if(temp->data < val){
            if(temp -> right == nullptr){
                temp->right = nn;
                return ;
            }
            temp = temp->right;
        }
        else
        {
            if(temp->left == nullptr)
            {
                temp->left = nn;
                return ;
            }
            
            temp = temp->left;
            
        }
        
    }
    
    return ;
    
}

void print(Node* temp,int val){
    
    if(temp == nullptr){
        return ;
    }
    
   if(temp->data == val){
       cout<<temp->data<<" "<<temp->left->data<<" "<<temp->right->data;
       return ;
   }
    
    print(temp->left,val);
    print(temp->right,val);
    
    return ;
}

int main(){
    
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    
    vector<int>arr(n);
    
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        cin>>arr[i];
        insert(arr[i]);
    }
    
    int u;
    cin>>u;
    
    print(root,u);
    
    
    
}
